==German==
===Etymology===
Modelled on other masculine nouns with feminine counterparts formed by the suffix ''-in'', after the gender of ''[[Gott]]'' was shifted by Christianity from neuter to masculine.
===Noun===
'''Göttin''' ''f'' (''plural'' Göttinnen)
# [[goddess]]

===Proper noun===
'''Gottin'''
# the [[Goddess]]

